{
  "texts": [
    "Large Language Models (LLMs) are advanced artificial intelligence systems designed to understand, generate, and interact with human language at a large scale.",
    "These models are trained on vast datasets of text, enabling them to learn a wide range of language patterns, structures, and nuances.",
    "LLMs use deep learning techniques, particularly neural networks, to process and produce language in a way that can mimic human-like understanding and responses (Hadi et al., 2023).",
    "Some examples of LLMs include ChatGPT (Open AI), Bert (Google), Electra (Google), RoBERTa (Meta), and ERNIE (Baidu).",
    "As LLMs continue to permeate various aspects of the education realm, integrating their use into course design holds immense promise (Rahman & Watanobe, 2023)."
  ]
}